The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimization of expected reward, which is a common topic in reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN), which falls under the category of deep learning and computer vision, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) possible sub-categories.
